        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43699",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've attached a patch for this component's test suite which illustrates the issue.  Here is the resulting testdox when I run those tests:\r\n{noformat}\r\n [x] Php locale en string type handles comma separator followed by two digits correctly\r\n [ ] Php locale en string type handles comma separator followed by three digits correctly\r\n [x] Php locale en string type handles comma separator followed by four digits correctly\r\n [x] Php locale en string type handles non zero number followed by comma separator followed by two digits correctly\r\n [ ] Php locale en string type handles non zero number followed by comma separator followed by three digits correctly\r\n [x] Php locale en string type handles non zero number followed by comma separator followed by four digits correctly\r\n{noformat}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-18T07:35:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-18T07:35:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43702",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm not entirely certain this is a bug.  The string '0,666' is a valid number (666), it's just that common convention would omit the '0,' as it's meaningless.  I'm not sure where that fits into the maintainer's vision of how Zend_Validate_Float should work. \r\n\r\nZend_Validate_Float::isValid() uses Zend_Locale_Data::isFloat(), which itself is just an alias of Zend_Locale_Data::isNumber(), which checks the number against the formats 'decimalnumber' and 'scientificnumber' in Zend\/Locale\/Data\/en.xml:\r\n{noformat}\r\n<decimalFormats>\r\n\t<decimalFormatLength>\r\n\t\t<decimalFormat>\r\n\t\t\t<pattern>#,##0.###<\/pattern>\r\n\t\t<\/decimalFormat>\r\n\t<\/decimalFormatLength>\r\n<\/decimalFormats>\r\n<scientificFormats>\r\n\t<scientificFormatLength>\r\n\t\t<scientificFormat>\r\n\t\t\t<pattern>#E0<\/pattern>\r\n\t\t<\/scientificFormat>\r\n\t<\/scientificFormatLength>\r\n<\/scientificFormats>\r\n{noformat}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-18T08:28:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-18T08:28:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43743",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Zend Framework defers this type of validation to Unicode's CLDR (http:\/\/cldr.unicode.org).  If you feel that the issue you have outlined here is indeed a bug which needs fixing, I would submit a bug report in CLDR's trac system at http:\/\/unicode.org\/cldr\/trac",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-19T12:09:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-19T12:09:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47879",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "According to the numeric rules in english a \",\" is treated as separator for thousand and above. Each 3 digits \"can\" be combined in a block separated by a \",\".\r\n\r\nThis means that values like \"0,666\" are logically converted into \"666\" as 0 for thousand is allowed and correct. It is allowed to have integer values within the float validator because integers are just a special variant of float values (en => 0,666 = 666 = 666.0)\r\n\r\nTherefor this is not an issue but expected behaviour.\r\nAs Adam said: When you feel that this is an failure in it's handling feel free to open a bug at unicode.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-08-06T05:47:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-08-06T05:47:39.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
